Seventeen people were injured in an accident at Amabuko near Keroka on the Kisii-Keroka highway on Wednesday. They were taken to the Kisii Teaching and Referral Hospital (pictured). A Nyamira Express bus rolled and landed in a valley. The bus had remained with 25 passengers after dropping the rest at various stopovers. Hospital chief executive Enock Ondari said 15 of the victims were treated and discharged. One patient with severe injuries is in a stable condition while another is still under special care. Keroka Base Commander Iltabul Kochale said the bus was from Nairobi headed to Sirare in Migori county.